[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Welcome to Masterful Moves: Gukesh"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]

{ Let's get started!Welcome to the wonderful world of Masterful Moves played by Gukesh. In this course we are going to see and learn from the tactics, strategies and playing style he has used to fulfil his promise as a prodigy and reach the top tier of the world chess elite. We are taking a journey with the Indian chess prodigy from his earliest days playing junior tournaments and onwards to his achieving the Grandmaster title, all the way to winning the board one gold medal at the Olympiad, twice, and his amazing victory at the Candidates in 2024 which took him to the World Championship match in Singapore. As we follow Gukeshâs development as a player, we will discover which factors set him apart from other players - including what he has learned from AlphaZero - and how his style gives rise to exciting tactics that you will be solving, learning from and, we believe, finding in your own games. In compiling this course we not only learned from Gukeshâs style, we also learned about his development as a player, the key tournaments he competed in that spurred his rapid increase in rating and the off-the-board factors that have contributed to his success. Weâll be sharing all those details with you, too. And we will find out what happened when Natasha met Gukesh and played a game against him. But first, do read through the Informationals in this section, particularly How to use this course. Thank you for buying this course. We hope you will enjoy it and will get as much learning from it as we have done from compiling it. WIM Natasha Regan and NI Matt Ball } 
1.--   *


[Event "Masterful Moves: Gukesh"]
[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Why Gukesh and his masterful moves?"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]

{ Why a course on Gukesh, his tactics and strategies?Gukesh has created a buzz in the international chess community with his exceptional talent and prodigious achievements at such a young age. His rise in the world of chess is nothing short of extraordinary. He became a Grandmaster in 2019 at the age of just 12 years, 7 months, and 17 days, making him one of the youngest ever to reach that level. While other prodigies also achieved titles at a young age, none has gone on to reach the World Championship match while still a teenager. Instructive style Gukeshâs aggressive and dynamic playing style also sets him apart. He is fearless and willing to take risks, often opting for bold and unconventional moves that can lead to tactical fireworks and unexpected twists or to a position where the opponent is so restricted that they can barely find a move to play. This approach not only makes his games highly entertaining to follow, but also instructive for players who would like to adopt a similar style. Gukeshâs achievements include: â¢ The third youngest player ever to become a Grandmaster. â¢ The youngest player to reach 2750. â¢ A double Olympiad individual gold medallist on board one. â¢ The youngest player ever to win the Candidates tournament. â¢ The youngest player ever to challenge for the world title. Young Indian talent He is also part of the thriving Indian chess scene, one of a number of young talents to have reached the upper echelons of the sport in the past few years. His development from beginner to World Championship contender in just over a decade sheds light on the ways in which the top prospects in India are nurtured and able to thrive, culminating in the team gold at the 2024 Olympiad where Indiaâs top three boards were: Gukesh, age 18; Praggnanandhaa, age 19; Arjun Erigaisi, age 21. There is no doubt that Gukesh is already an inspiration both to legions of fans and to a new generation of Indian juniors, some of whom will become household names in world chess in years to come and probably sooner than we think!. Complexity, tactics and AlphaZero Gukesh is widely known for his love of complexity, his ability to calculate tactics and his uncompromising style of play. In this course you can solve and enjoy more than 150 sequences from Gukeshâs tournament games. You will become more familiar with Gukeshâs style and what he aims for in a position â from activating his queen while keeping his opponentâs forces constrained, to rapidly advancing his pawns so they become dangerous attacking units. We track Gukeshâs journey from his early tournaments and his search for title norms to becoming an elite grandmaster challenging for the World Championship. Through the puzzles, we follow Gukeshâs increasingly sophisticated play, including his adoption of AlphaZero techniques and his handling of crucial games at the Candidates and the Olympiad. We also detail the off the board factors that have contributed to his extraordinary chess development - from the right mental attitude and his role models, to his preference for not using an engine in his calculation training and the astonishing number of games he played to achieve his norms. } 
