{ How this course was compiledHere are the sources we used to put this course together. The games We played through hundreds of Gukeshâs games to find interesting tactics. As we did so, we noticed a number of recurring motifs in Gukesh's style that we have highlighted for you in this course. The games were sourced from: ChessBase MegaDatabasechess.comchess-results.com365chess.com Tournaments, ratings and players Within the course we provide information including tournament results, playersâ ratings and playersâ biographies Tournament results were sourced from: chess.comchess-results.com365chess.comfide.comtournamentsâ own websites Playersâ ratings and titles were sourced from fide.com; other biographical information was found on chess.com, chessbase.com, chessbase.in and wikipedia.com Background on Gukesh For information on Gukeshâs career and games, and background on family and coaches we watched many hours of interviews on YouTube, we listened to podcasts and read articles in magazines and online. The main sources include: ChessBase IndiaWorld ChessFIDENew In ChessChess magazineGothamChess Testing We used a small team of beta-testers to read the courseâs text and play through the puzzles. All of them are players who we know personally and are active Chessable users. Their feedback and suggestions have been invaluable. Our thanks to Andrew, Nick, Phil and Steve. } 
