{ The march of the h-pawnGukesh has always been a fan of advancing his pawns and of targeting the opposing king. He uses the h-pawn sometimes to open up or expose the opposing king - for example in the game against Shahil Dey, where the h-pawn stops White from defending. Sometimes Gukesh plays an alternative plan, popularised by AlphaZero, where he pushes the h-pawn to [h6], which restricts the opposing king to the back rank, and controls the [g7] square, potentially setting up mates on that square - see the game against Mikhalevski. Gukesh Dommaraju - Victor Mikhalevski 2022 Gukesh has pushed his h-pawn all the way to [h6], AlphaZero style. This set-up leaves an ever-present danger for Black of the white queen landing on [g7] to deliver checkmate. Gukesh engineers a fork of this square with an undefended bishop on [b7]. Shahil Dey - Gukesh Dommaraju 2022 I like this example because it looks like Gukesh's h-pawn is nonchalantly not doing anything much, but White is then surprisingly powerless to meet Black's attack. Gukesh lines up his queen and bishop on the [b8]-[h2] diagonal to target [h2] and the white king. White is unable to defend with [g3] because of... Black's advanced h-pawn. The attack is soon terminal. Dmitry Frolyanov - Gukesh Dommaraju, 2018 In this game played before AlphaZero times, Gukesh has advanced his h-pawn to [h4] where it constrains White's kingside, and in particular means the defence of the [b8]-[h2] diagonal cannot be shored up with [g3]. Gukesh prepares to violently remove the defending knight on [f3] and White interposes a bishop to stop it... so Gukesh snaps that off too! Gukesh Dommaraju - Ojasva Singh, 2022 In several games, Gukesh used his advanced h-pawn to support a knight joining the attack from [g5]. In this game, the knight was captured and Gukesh followed up with an intermediate move bringing in the queen, and a fierce attack ensued. Moves from Gukesh - Mikhalevski 2022: } Bxg5  
2.Bxg5  Qxg5  
3.Qb2  {[%cal Bb2b7]} {[%csl Rb7]} {[%cal Bb2g7]} {[%csl Rg7]} {[%cal Bh6g7]}  *


