{ Sacrifices to attack the kingGukesh excels at finishing off the game clinically if there is a win in the position, and even his earliest games are full of sacrifices to reach the enemy king. Gukesh has trained tactics and also studied the classics - to good effect. When a classic pattern from a Lasker game recurred in his game against Prraneeth, Gukesh quickly found the winning sequence. Prraneeth Vuppalla - Gukesh Dommaraju 2017 Gukesh - aged 11 - plays a double bishop sacrifice in the style of Lasker! This blasts open his opponent's king and mate quickly follows. There is a wonderful YouTube video where Sagar Shah interviews Gukesh after the game and he reels off Lasker's moves from memory. Gukesh Dommaraju - Catherina Michelle 2017 As part of a pretty combination, Gukesh plays an exchange sacrifice to remove Black's most active defender, a knight, and to leave her with major pieces that are not in a position to help her king. Yahor Silich - Gukesh Dommaraju 2018 Black advances his g-pawn and then gives White an exchange on [e3]. In return, Gukesh gets some of his favourite goodies: a far advanced passed pawn, open lines against White's king, targetting the [g3]-pawn, and dominant control of the nearby dark squares. Gukesh Dommaraju - Sohel Chowdhury 2021 White's pieces are developed and pointing at the kingside whereas Black's are rather cramped and still undeveloped on the queenside. Gukesh knows that he can break through quickly and effectively. He sacrifices one piece and then another to break the black king's pawn cover. Then brings in his major pieces to deliver checkmate. Moves from Gukesh - Chowdhury 2021: } 
1.Nxe6  fxe6  
2.Bxh7+  Kxh7  
3.Qh3+   *


