26.Qxg4  Qxg4+  { White resigned in this game from the under 11 Indian Championship 2017. Prraneeth Vuppala, who became a Grandmaster in 2023, finished the tournament with 7.5/11. Gukesh won the tournament with 9/11 and a better tie-break than Pranav Venkatesh, Pranesh M and Leon Mendonca who finished on the same score and all of whom later became Grandmasters. In a YouTube interview with Chessbase India, Gukesh recalled the moves from the game Emanuel Lasker - Johann Bauer, Amsterdam 1889, in which Lasker delivered a similar double bishop sacrifice. } { In this position Lasker, White to play, stunned his opponent with 15.Bxh7+! 15...Kxh7 16.Qxh5+ Kg8 17.Bxg7! Lasker went on to finish it off from here, with Black resigning on move 38. }  0-1


