50.Qxg4+  Kf6  
51.Qf4+  { Black resigned. His king and knight will be forked next move. Other choices lead to a forced mating sequence. } Kg6  
52.Be8+  Kg7  
53.Qf7+  Kh8  
54.Qf6+  Kg8  
55.Bf7+  Kf8  
56.Bg6+  Kg8  
57.Qf7+  Kh8  
58.Qxh7  { That tournament took place from December 3-9, giving him fewer than three weeks to secure a third GM norm to become the youngest Grandmaster ever. An opportunity came at the Sunway Sitges tournament which ran from December 14-23 in Spain, but he drew his must-win, ninth-round game, missing the norm by half a point. âI was disappointed for two days,â Gukesh told ESPN. âThen I moved on.â }  *


[Event "Masterful Moves: Gukesh"]
[White "4) Age 11-12. The hunt for norms, 2018"]
[Black "More about Gukesh: 3. Playing a lot of games"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]

{ Playing a lot of gamesIn his pursuit of title norms and an increased rating, between 2017 and 2019 Gukesh played 589 FIDE-rated standard-play games, more than one every other day. In 2018 he hit a peak of 222 FIDE-rated games in 12 months, an extraordinary number as he chased down the International Master and Grandmaster titles. This would have been a whirlwind adventure for a boy who was not yet a teenager. The excitement of travelling from tournament to tournament and country to country; with no schoolwork to think about, Gukesh could focus solely on playing the game he loves so much } { (while his father took care of all the logistics) } { . In 2018 Gukesh played in tournaments held in locations such as Greece, Thailand, Russia, the Czech Republic, Spain, Abu Dhabi, Serbia, Gibraltar and the Isle of Man. Although chess can feel a high-pressured environment particularly when there is a Grandmaster world record at stake, at the age of 12 this would have been such an exhilarating time and momentum was in his favour. As the year progressed and he racked up more and more tournament appearances, his rating kept on rising and the dream of achieving the Grandmaster title loomed ever larger. Overall, since 2013 up to August 2023 he has played 1472 FIDE-rated standard-play games. He has also played 373 FIDE-rated blitz games and 192 FIDE-rated rapid games, contributing to more than 2,000 games under his name in the MegaDatabase. He would also have played hundreds or thousands of other online or over-the-board games. In general, that might be quite typical for a high-level player active over a long period but the number of games he fitted in during the time he was chasing the titles is eye-catching. } 
1.--   *


