20.Ng7+  { A brilliant deflection tactic!! It might not be everybody's first thought to play the knight in to [g7], but it forces the black bishop to leave its defensive duties blocking the e-file. } ( { Instead } 20.Nf6+ Bxf6 { is not effective here, as from [f6] the black bishop covers the [e7] square. } ) ( { Another nice move for White in the starting position is } 20.Bb5 { , } { to deflect the [d7]-bishop from the defence of [e6]. It is strong, but not as good as the game continuation. } ) ( { If instead White plays } 20.Be3 gxh5 { , then Black gets a winning position. } ) ( { Other moves with the dark squared bishop fail to Black's battery on the c-file such as: } 20.Bb4 20...Qxc1 ) Bxg7  ( { No better is } 20...Kd8 21.Nxe6+ Bxe6 22.Qxe6 Re8 23.Qxd5+ ) 
21.Rxe6+  Kd8  ( { Taking the rook leads immediately to a forced mating line that begins: } 21...Bxe6 22.Qxe6+ Kd8 23.Be7+ Ke8 24.Bb5+ ) 
22.Be7+  {[%cal Be7d8]} {[%csl Rd8]} {[%cal Be6e8]} {[%csl Re8]} { The black queen will be lost. } Ke8  
23.Bd6+  Kd8  
