{ Gukesh has built up a strong black pawn centre. How does he respond to White's last move 42. [Qf3] ? } Rb1+  { Forces the White king to h2, which will help to mobilise the pawn centre next move, as the king will now be in the path of a bishop pin from e5. Also good here is 42...[e4] which will likely transpose. } 
43.Kh2  e4  
