35.Qxb5  ( { There are three approaches you might take: Attacking, exchanging or defensive. The defensive path is not very good here as it allows Black to get the edge. For example too passive is: } 35.Qc2 Qa4 { when continuing a defensive path gets into trouble e.g. } 36.Qe2 Qa1 { with advantage. } ) ( { The exchanging path leads to a roughly level endgame after: } 35.Qxa3 Nxa3 36.exd5 exd5 { . } { Gukesh chose the attacking path. He spotted the amazing concept of giving up his knight on [c1] to generate counterplay against the weak [f7] square and the black king. With best play it is level, but we will see that Black makes an error along the way. } ) Qxc1+  
