80.Ke4  {[%cal Be5g6]} {[%cal Bg6e7]} {[%cal Bg6f8]} {[%cal Bf7f8]} {[%csl Re7]} {[%csl Rf8]} {[%cal Ra3f3]} {[%cal Be4f3]} { Black resigned. This was an impressive win by Gukesh. He choose to go into this two knights versus a rook endgame, which he could so easily have lost, and proceeded to grind away with little time remaining on either player's clock. He forced a mistake from his opponent and played only move after only move to finish it off. The result gave India a 2.5 - 1.5 victory over China in round 7 of the 2024 Olympiad. Here is what the commentators had to say about Gukesh's performance: 'At the board he is a stone cold killer...he may be young, but his age belies his experience, his strength. He is phenomenal.' - GM Robert Hess 'I am honestly in absolute awe watching this' - GM Peter Svidler 'Put some respect on that man's name. This is an achievement that even Magnus Carlsen would consider among his best. This endgame conversion has been un-freaking-believable.' GM Daniel Naroditsky }  1-0


